div.p:
(1) Have dropped some terms the U.S. had objected to (e.g., single-purpose,
                    dual-purpose, teratogen, carcinogen), but have retained others (e.g., chemical
                    agent);

(2) Have agreed to put precursors under the general purpose criterion and have
                    accepted, in principle, the U.S. proposal for a list of “important” precursors
                    to serve as a focus for verification efforts;
